
[1]rite

   RITE, n. [L. ritus.]

   The manner of performing divine or solemn service as established by
   law, precept or custom; formal act of religion, or other solemn duty.
   The rites of the Israelites were numerous and expensive; the rites of
   modern churches are more simple. Funeral rites are very different in
   different countries. The sacrament is a holy rite.
